<br>
I agree wholeheartedly. I like to make several characters on a server I'm planning to join - run them up to about 10th level each, that way I can get a feel of the population. Can't do that here. <br>
<br>
But in a way that's good. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubormwarrior.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Borm Warrior</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/18/02 10:14:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1138.topic&index=14>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why we love FV</span><hr size=1> The single character is the best thing about our server for me. We have a small population and when that is combined with a single character per account you have the best possible personal accountability in the game. <br>
<br>
In FV you are only as good as your reputation. Couple that with the language barriers and you have some great fun. When Borm as a level 12 in the Warrens he did something to offend some elf. I had no idea what it could have been, it was obviously not intentional, nonetheless, given the language barriers we could not communicate to try and smooth things out.<br>
<br>
At first that upset me, I needed to try and fix it. Then it struck me that this way was much more complex. I would either have to be creative and try to fix things or live with the knowledge that I might never be able to fix it. This server forces us to do new and different things, to grow as an EQ player. <br>
<br>
Borm, still most likely a goat in some poor elf's eyes! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arios</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 400<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/18/02 10:30:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1138.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why we love FV</span><hr size=1> I love the single character limit, I love the way it stops twinking BUT I do have 1 dislike.<br>
<br>
I hate the way friends decide that they would like to try X and delete their 40+ characters to start all over again <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
This is something I find depressing. Me, well I will never delete any character I have ever made anywhere. Hell I even have issues with deleteing mules. I see so many people re starting this has 2 effects.<br>
<br>
1. Guarentees a continued low lvl population (which is not a bad thing, I have also noticed there are quite a few newbies both from other servers and TRULY new :-)<br>
<br>
2. It depletes folks from the higher level ranges. I hope enough people hang on or buy second accounts so there is a viable bigger population.<br>
<br>
That said I love the low pop :-) love going to dungeons and there being only the team I have brought with me. Love languages, love TLC (though it has bitten me a couple of times).<br>
<br>
With TLC I find there are many younger folks who if you get to know them are more than welcome to do quests for you even if they are not guilded with you. And if you are guilded, even easier :-)<br>
<br>
I love FV.<br>
<br>
Its my last best chance for EQ :-)<br>
<br>
